'''Kudret <U+00D6>zersay''' (born 16 December 1973) is a [[Turkish Cypriot]] academic, diplomat and politician. <U+00D6>zersay is running for [[President of Northern Cyprus]] in [[Northern Cyprus presidential election, 2015|April's elections]]. Until October 2014, he was the chief Turkish Cypriot negotiator for the settlement of the [[Cyprus dispute]]. After his announcement of his candidacy, President [[Dervi<U+015F> Ero<U+011F>lu]] removed him from his post.<ref>{{cite news|title=Turkish-Cypriot leader fires chief negotiator in peace talks|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/4dcgi/_w_articles_wsite1_1_08/10/2014_543553|accessdate=31 January 2015|work=Kathimerini English Edition|date=8 October 2014}}</ref> <U+00D6>zersay had been involved in the negotiations since 2003.<ref>{{cite web|title=INTERVIEW: Turkish Cypriot mediator Ozersay on Cyprus peace talks|url=http://www.worldbulletin.net/interviews-in-depth/143296/interview-turkish-cypriot-mediator-ozersay-on-cyprus-peace-talks|website=Worldbulletin News|accessdate=31 January 2015}}</ref>

==Education==
<U+00D6>zersay studied international relations at [[Ankara University]]. His 2002 PhD thesis was on the "Validity of the 1959<U+2013>1960 Cyprus Treaties In International Law".<ref>{{cite web|title=Kudret <U+00D6>zersay <U+2013> Curriculum Vitae|url=http://ir.emu.edu.tr/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Kudret-Ozersay-cv.pdf|accessdate=31 January 2015}}</ref>

